gan]] || Coach<br>Manager || 1985\u20131988<br>1988\u20131991 \n|-\n| 2 || [[Jerry Remy]] || [[Second baseman|2B]]<br>Broadcaster || 1978\u20131984<br>1988\u2013present\n|-\n| 5, 15, 39 || [[George Scott (first baseman)|George Scott]] || [[First baseman|1B]] || 1966\u20131971<br>1977\u20131979\n|-\n| 5 || [[Vern Stephens]] || [[Shortstop|SS]] || 1948\u20131952\n|-\n| 16 || style=\"background:#ffb;\"|'''[[Dick Williams]]''' || [[Outfielder|OF]]/[[Third baseman|3B]]<br>Manager || 1963\u20131964<br>1967\u20131969\n|-\n|Moment:<br>10/17/2004\n|[[Dave Roberts (outfielder)|Dave Roberts]]\n|Pinch-run stolen base to start bottom of the 9th inning rally in Game 4 of the 2004 ALCS vs the New York Yankees\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\" |2008 || \u2014 ||[[George J. Digby|George Digby]]|| Scout || 1944\u20132009\n|-\n| 12 || [[Wes Ferrell]] || [[Pitcher|P]] || 1934\u20131937\n|-\n| 37, 39 || [[Mike Greenwell]] || [[Left fielder|LF]] || 1985\u20131996\n|-\n| \u2014 || [[Edward F. Kenney, Sr.|Edward Kenney, Sr.]] || Executive || 1948\u20131991\n|-\n| 37 || [[Bill Lee (left-handed pitcher)|Bill Lee]] || [[Pitcher|P]] || 1969\u20131978\n|-\n| \u2014 || [[Everett Scott]] || [[Shortstop|SS]] || 1914\u20131921\n|-\n| 18, 30 || [[Frank Sullivan (baseball)|Frank Sullivan]] || [[Pitcher|P]] || 1953\u20131960\n|-\n| 42 || [[Mo Vaughn]] || [[First baseman|1B]] || 1991\u20131998\n|-\n|Moment:<br>9/28/1960\n|[[Ted Williams]]\n|Hits a home run in final major league at-bat vs the Baltimore Orioles\n|\n|-\n|Moment:<br>10/19/2004\n|[[Curt Schilling]]\n|\"Bloody Sock\" Performance in Game 6 of the 2004 ALCS vs the New York Yankees\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2010 || 4 ||[[Tommy Harper]]||[[Outfielder|OF]]/[[Third baseman|3B]]|| 1972\u20131974\n|-\n| 2, 12 || [[Eddie Kasko]] || [[Shortstop|SS]]/[[Third baseman|3B]]<br>Manager || 1966<br>1970\u20131973\n|-\n| 2, 24, 26, 34, 37 || [[Jimmy Piersall]] || [[Center fielder|CF]] || 1950, 1952\u20131958\n|-\n| 13 || [[John Valentin]] || [[Shortstop|SS]]/[[Third ba